              </div>
            </details>

            <details itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
              <summary itemprop="name">What is e-waste recycling and why is it important in Kochi?</summary>
              <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq-answer">
                <p itemprop="text">E-waste recycling is the certified process of recovering valuable materials from discarded electronics while safely neutralizing hazardous components like lead, mercury and cadmium. In Kochi, which generates over 18,000 metric tonnes of e-waste annually, proper recycling prevents toxic contamination of the Periyar river basin and ensures compliance with India's E-Waste Rules 2022.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset class="faq-category">
            <legend>Pickup & Pricing</legend>
            
            <details itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
              <summary itemprop="name">How does your e-waste collection service work?</summary>
              <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq-answer">
                <p itemprop="text">Simply contact us to schedule a pickup. We arrive with proper documentation, collect your e-waste, and provide a Certificate of Destruction within 24 hours. For 10+ devices, pickup is free.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
              <summary itemprop="name">Is e-waste disposal free for businesses?</summary>
              <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq-answer">
                <p itemprop="text">We offer free pickup for 10 or more devices. Every job includes a Certificate of Destruction at no extra cost.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
              <summary itemprop="name">How quickly can you collect e-waste from my office?</summary>
              <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq-answer">
                <p itemprop="text">Same-day to 48-hour turnaround is standard. We also offer 4-hour emergency service for urgent corporate needs.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
              <summary itemprop="name">Where is the best e-waste collection point in Kochi?</summary>
              <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq-answer">
                <p itemprop="text">Our main facility is at 710A, Hill Palace Road, Thrippunithura, Kochi — open Monday to Saturday 8AM–8PM, Sunday 10AM–4PM. For corporate clients in Infopark, Smart City and Kakkanad, we offer free same-day pickup. For residential areas across Ernakulam, we pick up within 24 hours of booking via WhatsApp.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </fieldset>

          <fieldset class="faq-category">
            <legend>Data Destruction & ITAD</legend>
            
            <details itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
              <summary itemprop="name">What does ITAD stand for and what does it include?</summary>
              <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq-answer">
                <p itemprop="text">ITAD stands for IT Asset Disposition — a certified, auditable process of retiring IT equipment. A complete ITAD service includes: asset inventory and tagging, NIST 800-88/DoD certified data destruction, Certificate of Destruction, KSPCB-compliant recycling, value recovery through buyback, and DPDP Act 2023 compliance documentation.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
              <summary itemprop="name">What is certified IT asset destruction for companies in Kochi?</summary>
              <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq-answer">
                <p itemprop="text">Certified IT asset destruction involves NIST 800-88 or DoD 5220.22-M data destruction of all storage media, followed by eco-responsible recycling, with a serial-numbered Certificate of Destruction issued for every device. EWaste Kochi provides this for all sizes — from a single laptop to a 500-device enterprise IT refresh at Infopark.</p>
              </div>
            </details>

            <details itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Question">
              <summary itemprop="name">Who is the best certified ITAD company in Kochi?</summary>
              <div itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/Answer" class="faq-answer">
                <p itemprop="text">EWaste Kochi is the preferred ITAD partner for 500+ businesses in Kochi and Kerala, including IT companies at Infopark, banks on MG Road, hospitals in Ernakulam and manufacturing firms in Kalamassery. We are KSPCB authorized, NIST 800-88 certified, and DPDP Act 2023 compliant — providing a complete audit trail needed for any corporate compliance review.</p>
              </div>
            </details>
          </fieldset>
        </div>
        
